headline: Nvidia post-earnings pricing, software stocks rise, IonQ jumps
summary: Yahoo Finance Senior Reporter Allie Canal covers Wednesday's top stocks and market movers in this Market Minute. Nvidia (NVDA) stock remains flat as investors await the company's second quarter earnings results, with options traders pricing in a $260–270 billion move, according to Reuters. Software stocks Snowflake (SNOW), Datadog (DDOG), and GitLab (GTLB) are climbing after MongoDB (MDB) and Okta (OKTA) beat estimates and raised earnings forecasts. IonQ (IONQ) stock jumps as B. Riley initiates coverage of the company with a Buy rating. Tune in to Yahoo Finance on Wednesday, Aug. 27 at 4:15 p.m. for special coverage of Nvidia's quarterly results, followed by an exclusive interview with Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang at 6:40 p.m. Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.

headline: NoBS.tech Achieves Datadog Premier Partner Status in Under Two Years
